THE NET UNREALIZED LOSSES AS OF SEPTEMBER 28, 2013 AND THE NET UNREALIZED GAINS AS OF

SEPTEMBER 29, 2012 ARE RELATED PRIMARILY TO LONG-TERM MARKETABLE SECURITIES. THE COMPANY MAY SELL CERTAIN OF ITS MARKETABLE SECURITIES PRIOR TO THEIR STATED MATURITIES FOR STRATEGIC REASONS INCLUDING, BUT NOT LIMITED TO, ANTICIPATION OF CREDIT

DETERIORATION AND DURATION MANAGEMENT. DURING 2013, 2012 AND 2011, THE NET REALIZED GAINS RECOGNIZED BY THE COMPANY WERE NOT SIGNIFICANT. THE MATURITIES OF THE COMPANYS LONG-TERM MARKETABLE SECURITIES GENERALLY RANGE FROM ONE TO FIVE YEARS.

